# HTB Theme - Mandatory for All UI

All components, styles, and generated code **must** use the Hack The Box colour scheme.

## Palette (use these only)

| Token | Hex/Value | Usage |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| `--htb-primary` | #0B121F | Main background, dark canvas |
| `--htb-accent` | #9FEF00 | Buttons, active states, highlights, headings |
| `--htb-secondary` | #A3B3BC | Muted text, borders, secondary UI |
| `--htb-text` | #FFFFFF | Main body text |
| `--htb-glow` | rgba(159,239,0,0.4) | Neon glow effects |
| `--htb-surface` | #111827 | Cards, panels, elevated surfaces |
| `--htb-border` | #1e293b | Borders, dividers |

## Tailwind Classes

- `bg-htb-primary`, `bg-htb-surface` — backgrounds
- `text-htb-text`, `text-htb-secondary`, `text-htb-accent` — text
- `border-htb-border`, `border-htb-accent` — borders
- `focus:ring-htb-accent`, `focus:border-htb-accent` — focus states
- `hover:text-htb-accent`, `hover:border-htb-accent` — hover states
- `htb-glow`, `htb-glow-text`, `htb-btn-accent` — custom utilities in globals.css

## Design Rules

- **Dark cyber aesthetic** — high contrast, sharp edges
- **Bold uppercase headings** — section titles
- **Neon green** for interactive elements (buttons, links, active)
- **No colours outside this palette** — avoid zinc, slate, red, blue, etc.
- **Errors/warnings** — use `htb-error-box` or accent at reduced opacity

## Example

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<button className="bg-htb-accent text-htb-primary font-semibold">Submit</button>
<section className="border border-htb-border bg-htb-surface p-4">
  <h2 className="text-htb-accent uppercase">Section</h2>
  <p className="text-htb-secondary">Muted text</p>
</section>

// ❌ Wrong
<button className="bg-blue-500">Submit</button>
<div className="bg-zinc-100 text-black">...</div>
```
